For a clear view of the ground, as it rushes upward. Paired with wind-blown hair, which is never going to be manageable again.
What Dwight once wore to his 9 to 5 is now a fashion statement with hipsters everywhere.
Dwight hated every single minute of his new job and the irritating fake ears only amplified his frustration.
Complimented by vintage-style glasses, Dwight manages to pull off what few men can—the trillby.
This trilby is so casual, so carefree, that one might mistake Dwight for someone more laid back.
A jolly Dwight, topped with a star.
A vivid cap to project confidence, which he does not possess.
While he dozed off, the fresh sea breeze brushed his thin straw hat from his face, revealing his pale skin to the full wrath of the midday sun.
Styling his hair like this took an hour: 58 minutes stressing out about what to do, and 2 minutes carelessly sweeping it over.
When the sweat started pouring an hour into a nature hike, he borrowed a bandana from an overprepared camper and wrapped it around his head.
A mask they found themselves wearing at the masquerade ball.
Bright red glasses to complete his holiday outfit. Time to celebrate!
The official cap of the Wildland Adventurers, still smelling of smoke and pinecones.
A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team

Description.LocalizedString: Pants that defy all notions of wear and tear.
Seamless, stretchy tights made of polyester materials that wick moisture away as Dwight cycles up cruel hills.
Naturally torn and dusted, these jeans are accidentally in style.
The stench of spilled gasoline from the few times Dwight overfilled a gas tank still lingers in the fabric. How long until the stench of blood overpowers it?
Just when Dwight thought things couldn't get worse, he ripped his tights. He had to borrow this pair of weathered, second-hand tights for the rest of his contract.
Dwight achieves business cool with rolled up jeans that show off his sleek new shoes.
Not a creature was stirring, not even Dwight’s slippers.
He ultimately found his way back to his meagre hostel a few hours later.

He hopped on each foot as he walked across the burning sand to set up his beach towel. After wrapping his burning toes into another towel, he laid down and fell asleep, leaving his legs completely bare.
What was intended to be a beautiful romantic gesture—a single rose—suddenly became a very uncomfortable seat.
There’s a pocket for everything on these: compass, canteen, loose trail mix, you name it.
These slacks aren’t made for crouching and hiding from a bloodthirsty killer, but nothing’s stopping Dwight from wearing them!
Pants that have traveled with Dwight through many adventures, such as the time he battled a raccoon for his trail mix.
